  "title": "Planning Engineer (Building/ P6)/ HQ 5 day/ Up to $7K basic+bonus/ Building Construction",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Up to Basic $7K+ Bonus!</strong></li><li><strong>Permanent position, Paya Lebar</strong></li><li><strong>HQ tenders or project site office.</strong></li><li><strong>p6 primavera/ MS project/ and Building project experiences preferred</strong></li><li><strong>Reputable MNCs and leading A1 main contractor</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the Planning Manager in all planning functions</li><li>Develop construction programmes for the projects</li><li>Liaise and coordinate with departments and project team to incorporate relevant information for the implementation of the project schedule</li><li>Prepare daily, weekly and monthly progress reports for internal and external stake holders.</li><li>Maintain and update all schedules, collect actual data (progress, manpower and equipment deployment) and evaluate project delays by effective monitoring of actual progress</li><li>Maintain records for all significant events relevant to contractual claims.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Civil Engineering and/or relevant field</li><li>Experience in construction planning and programme for civil work or infrastructure projects.</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information:</strong></p><p><strong>To apply please click on the APPLY NOW button or email your resume to </strong><a href=\"mailto:search5@searchindex.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>search84@searchindex.com.sg</strong></a><strong> with the following detail:</strong></p><p>· Reason for leaving each past & current employment</p><p>· Salary drawn for each past & current employment</p><p>· Expected Salary</p><p>· Earliest availability date</p><p><strong>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</strong></p><p><strong>Lionel Cheow</strong></p><p><strong>EA License | 14C7092</strong></p><p><strong>EA Registration Number | R1105005</strong></p>",
